data.title: Always a Great Time
data.text: We are becoming regulars here. Good food, great service close to home. Who could ask for more. There Friday happy hour times are an event so things can get tight but well worth any wait you have to put up with.

data.title: Best breakfast!
data.text: I went here with a group of friends for breakfast and we all thought it was amazing! Everything I tried, from the chicken fried steak to stuffed french toast to the biscuits & gravy I ordered, was oustanding. The gravy was to die for and the biscuits were soft but not soggy. On top of that our waitress was super cool and provided excellent service! We were all really glad we came here and I can't wait to come back!

data.title: NIce Place - Great Staff
data.text: Stopped in here with friends for drinks and appetizers - so glad we did!  What a great friendly, helpful staff, plenty of appetizer options on the menu (wings were super!), good selection of beers on tap, good mixed drinks.  Just a nice, classy neighborhood bar/ I look forward to going again!

data.title: Good food & service
data.text: The hostess, drink guy and waitress were all very attentive,  I ordered the special which was crab cakes,  potatoes and vegtables. I was happy that the vegtables were asparagus & carrots and although they were a little hard for my liking,  they were very tasty.  The crab cakes were delicious!

data.title: Classy all-american restaurant
data.text: We love Redmond's!  Their wait-staff is one of the friendliest in the area, and they have a large variety in food and drink choices.  AND everything always tastes great!

data.title: nice chill place
data.text: great ambience, open late! the late night selection wasn't huge but it was comfort food, libe music, and comfortable seating! can't get better n redmond.

data.title: Nice upscale establisment for a work ( business) dinner outing.
data.text: Was here for happy hour.   Nachos had huge plate piled high. Wings were hot and crispy.   Lettuce wrap was OK.   Seared ahi was OK... Salad on the side was yummy.

data.title: Mid Level
data.text: We visited this restaurant for an impropmto lunch in July of last year.  Its not a dive bar as other reviews have said but its also not fancy.  The food was fine and the service was fine.  The prices were mid level.

data.title: Not a dive bar, not a fancy bar
data.text: This is a great mid-tier bar (not dive, not fancy).  They have good higher quality food and a good beer selection.  They also have a lot of TVs to catch the game.

data.title: Great local pub with better than average food and service.
data.text: Redmond's has become our go-to place for a laid back meal and drinks in Redmond. The staff is great, the food is varied and delicious. The place has a good energy overall and we always walk out happy. We tried brunch once when the Village Café was jammed (as usual) and decided that Redmond's is now our first choice.

data.title: Crowded with bad service and mediocre food
data.text: We went to RBC on a Saturday night, based on reviews and a coupon that I had.  The place was very crowded.  The wait for 2 people was 20 min and for 4 was an hour.  Since there were 2 of us we waited.  It was too crowded to wait inside so we sat outside and the called us when a table was ready.  We were seated at a row of tables next to the bar.  It was extremely noisy with a lot of waitstaff rushing past on both sides.  I ordered a glass of Chardonnay which was at room temperature.  We ordered their hanger steaks. My husband ordered well done with veggies, fries and a salad for $ extra. I ordered medium done, mashed potatoes and a salad subbed for veggies. Both orders had mashed potatoes, one with veggies which he put in front of me. I checked the steak on both. We asked about the order.  He said he would bring out an order of fries.  Then it seemed maybe that I had my husband's plate.  The steak on both plates was the about the same as far as rare/done - about medium or medium well, so I switched plates.  The mashed potatoes were the same temperature as the wine - lukewarm. My husbands veggies were the same lukewarm temp.  The steak had a sauce that looked like it would be good.  It didn't have much flavor at all.  Fortunately the coupon made the price so it was okay - $60 for that meal was way too much. I don't plan on going back.

data.title: LOVE Brunch & Happy Hour
data.text: We take all of our out of town guests here for late night happy hour. Great food and drink options. Love the portions and the service is always great. Went to brunch for the first time last month and we LOVED it. Better than the cafes we've been going to. Definitely our new go-to brunch place on the eastside!

data.title: Good location for Sunday breakfast
data.text: Serves breakfast until 2pm on Sunday. Takes reservations so can be settled in for the SeaHawks game. Excellent service. Good food. Great price.

data.title: Good Sports Bar with Decent Sandwich
data.text: We ate at Redmond’s on a recent Thursday night.    We arrived about 6.  The bar has quite a few TV’s featuring two large screens.  The Thursday night NFL game was on all the TV’s but based on my request they found us a smaller TV to put on the college game and got us a prime table to watch it.  The bar is pretty loud with the games on so be prepared.  It did not bother me but I could see how some folks might not like it.  I had the French Dip and it was an excellent sandwich.  The fries were a little over done but they were tasty.  It’s a sports bar with decent food and it was a good place to watch the game.  Our waitress was very attentive.  Somewhere I could go back for a sandwich and to watch a game.

data.title: Good food but slow service
data.text:
We have eaten here for dinner and breakfast and have been happy with both. The food is good with gluten free options. The menu has plenty of verity for a pub atmosphere. The servers are nice and everyone smiles, but the service has been slow every time we came in.
Definitely try it because the food and atmosphere are worth it.

data.title: Great lunch specials and beer selection
data.text: RBG turned out to be a great idea for lunch.  They have some good food specials and their beer selection is over the top.  Try the pastrami sandwich and garlic parm fries. Many TV's as well for sports.  A welcome addition to Redmond's bland bar scene.

data.title: Busy, fun atmosphere!
data.text: I've eaten at Redmond's Bar & Grill twice now and had good food & service!  The burgers & fries I've ordered are excellent and there are many more enticing entries on the menu to try!  IMO, this is a "down-home" kind of place that's more about meeting friends for a good dinner and drinks than more upscale places where you fell obligated to order vodka martinis specifying Grey Goose!

data.title: Good Stuff
data.text:
First, parking in this part of Downtown Redmond is challenging.  The best place to park is kitty-corner across the street at the repair shop where this is assigned parking for three restaurants.  Or, about a block away where there is 2 hour parking on Redmond Way.  Redmond Way is a one way street so the lot is east of the restaurant.  There is limited street parking. 

There is limited outside seating, but larger inside with more of a sports bar feeling.  Very nice inside with a warm greeting and friendly staff. 
 
There are a variety of items on the menu to satisfy varied palettes depending on your appetite.   We went with the hanger steak and the lasagne.  Both were very good and we would get them both again.  The lasagne is a large portion so some will be going home with you.

data.title: Great time and awesome staff
data.text: Really like to have team events here and bring friends. Love this place. I always get treated right and have a great experience.

data.title: Surprised!
data.text: We went to this restaurant expecting the usual sports bar and grill fare.  But we were very suprised with the quality and variety of the food and friendliness of the wait staff.  Out of the four of us 3 had the beef dip sandwich and I had the chicken gyro.  The beef was very tender and my chicken was done just right and juicy in the middle. They serve local beers and our friend said the dark beer he had was delicious. The fries are very good crucnhy outside and tender inside.  The price is very modest.  Great place for lunch or dinner.  We will be going back.
